CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 3, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "Aurora Club Holds 65th Celebration - Aurora Members - When the Aurora Reading Club gave its musicale and reception, observing the 65th year of its existence, these members were on hand at the Stephen Foster Memorial Hall. Front row:  Mmes. David Alter, Edward Jeffries, Abram T. Hall, new president, James Stevenson; outgoing president, W. Roderick Brown; Nathan Brown, Clifton Morrison, Luther Johnson and Lois White Buchanan.  Second row: Miss Carolyn Lovett, Mmes. Henry Bridges, Samuel Parr, J. W. Peyton and Samuel Golden.  Last row: Mmes. Homer S. Brown, Clarence Burrell, Nathaniel Dandridge and T. Wilson Primas. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Aurora Reading Club members, front row: Mrs. David Alter, Mrs. Edward Jeffries, Mrs. Abram T. Hall, Mrs. James Stevenson, Mrs. W. Roderick Brown, Mrs. Nathan Brown, Mrs. Clifton Morrison, Maudelena Johnson, Lois White Buchanan; second row: Carolyn Lovett, Mrs. Henry Bridges, Mrs. Samuel Parr, Mrs. J. W. Peyton, Lois Golden; last row: Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Mrs. Clarence Burrell, Helen Dandridge, and Edwina Primas
